build SGLang Gemma4 source-stack image	Build and push image	2026-06-12T16:23:17.9315944Z #13 42.33 The packages provided here are loosely based on the debian upstream packages with some modifications to make them more usable as non-default pythons and on ubuntu.  As such, the packages follow debian's patterns and often do not include a full python distribution with just `apt install python#.#`.  Here is a list of packages that may be useful along with the default install:
build SGLang Gemma4 source-stack image	Build and push image	2026-06-12T16:23:17.9318106Z #13 42.33 
build SGLang Gemma4 source-stack image	Build and push image	2026-06-12T16:23:17.9321584Z #13 42.33 - `python#.#-dev`: includes development headers for building C extensions
build SGLang Gemma4 source-stack image	Build and push image	2026-06-12T16:23:17.9322414Z #13 42.33 - `python#.#-venv`: provides the standard library `venv` module
build SGLang Gemma4 source-stack image	Build and push image	2026-06-12T16:23:17.9323194Z #13 42.33 - `python#.#-distutils`: provides the standard library `distutils` module
build SGLang Gemma4 source-stack image	Build and push image	2026-06-12T16:23:17.9324250Z #13 42.33 - `python#.#-lib2to3`: provides the `2to3-#.#` utility as well as the standard library `lib2to3` module
build SGLang Gemma4 source-stack image	Build and push image	2026-06-12T16:23:17.9325365Z #13 42.33 - `python#.#-gdbm`: provides the standard library `dbm.gnu` module
build SGLang Gemma4 source-stack image	Build and push image	2026-06-12T16:23:17.9326130Z #13 42.33 - `python#.#-tk`: provides the standard library `tkinter` module
build SGLang Gemma4 source-stack image	Build and push image	2026-06-12T16:23:17.9326703Z #13 42.33 
build SGLang Gemma4 source-stack image	Build and push image	2026-06-12T16:23:17.9327056Z #13 42.33 Third-Party Python Modules
